place.name: ALDBOROUGH
place.gazetteerText: ALDBOROUGH, a parish in Erpingham district, Norfolk; on the river Bure, 4¾ miles N by W of Aylsham, and 7 NW of N. Walsham r. station. It has a post office under Norwich. Acres, 788. Real property, £2,051. Pop., 305. Houses, 79. The property is subdivided. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £173.* Patron, Lord Suffield. The church was restored in 1849. There is a P. Methodist chapel. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
